WEBVTT

00:01.869 --> 00:02.735
Nick got kidnapped two days ago,
and what do I do?

00:02.737 --> 00:03.336
Get high for two days.

00:03.338 --> 00:04.603
We both did.

00:04.605 --> 00:06.339
I have my<i> tías</i>
in San Antonio.

00:06.341 --> 00:07.740
The ones in Texas?

00:07.742 --> 00:10.009
Renn, you're not taking
Nick to Texas.

00:10.011 --> 00:11.610
He's our brother.

00:11.612 --> 00:12.611
He's not.

00:12.613 --> 00:13.946
It's disgusting.

00:13.948 --> 00:15.548
Tommy:
Got an idea for another job.

00:15.550 --> 00:16.882
Go home, alright?
What?

00:16.884 --> 00:19.018
Hey, don't touch me!
You're fired.

00:19.020 --> 00:21.754
Drive safe.
Alright.
Hey, good luck.

00:21.756 --> 00:24.757
She's beautiful --
your girlfriend.

00:24.759 --> 00:27.360
Louise: All you have to do
is admit to what happened.

00:27.362 --> 00:28.627
I think you want to.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.229
That's why you told Amy.

00:30.231 --> 00:32.765
I followed her home
that night you two had dinner.

00:32.767 --> 00:34.166
She didn't want
to tell me,

00:34.168 --> 00:36.635
but you made her
an accessory to the crime.

00:36.637 --> 00:37.970
What else
was she gonna do?

00:37.972 --> 00:39.905
Andrew Cody's gonna
spend the night with us.

00:39.907 --> 00:41.707
On what legal basis?

00:41.709 --> 00:43.508
Confessed to the murder
of Catherine Belen.

00:43.510 --> 00:45.177
You stole from us.

00:45.179 --> 00:46.311
Your shit's loose.

00:46.313 --> 00:49.048
-Talked to Pete.
-[ Grunting ]

00:50.651 --> 00:52.552
J: He took Pete's eye out.

00:53.854 --> 00:57.590
♪♪

00:57.592 --> 01:03.528
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:03.530 --> 01:07.466
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:07.468 --> 01:10.536
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:13.274 --> 01:18.944
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:18.946 --> 01:22.547
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:22.549 --> 01:25.785
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:29.556 --> 01:32.225
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:32.227 --> 01:36.095
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:36.097 --> 01:39.965
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:39.967 --> 01:43.702
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:43.704 --> 01:47.840
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:47.842 --> 01:51.644
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:51.646 --> 01:53.880
♪ Got a ♪

01:59.520 --> 02:00.720
Finnigan.

02:04.191 --> 02:06.125
Finnigan: You guys
got something for me?

02:06.127 --> 02:07.726
Deran: We're going to see Pope
at County later.

02:07.728 --> 02:11.130
We wanted to get an update
on protection.

02:11.132 --> 02:13.732
People are looking out
for him.

02:13.734 --> 02:16.068
Your brother isn't exactly
a willing participant.

02:16.070 --> 02:18.137
-What do you mean?
-Doesn't seem to want the help.

02:18.139 --> 02:20.605
He's not
thinking straight.

02:20.607 --> 02:22.141
I'll talk to him.

02:22.143 --> 02:23.876
Any trouble
from La Familia?

02:23.878 --> 02:28.013
No. Maybe they decided
to let the whole eye thing go.

02:28.015 --> 02:29.748
Or there's nobody
connected to Pete

02:29.750 --> 02:31.817
in his unit
at County right now.

02:31.819 --> 02:32.818
We're on it.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.353
Who's Pope bunking with?

02:34.355 --> 02:35.888
Just my guy right now.

02:35.890 --> 02:38.157
They're gonna try and send
a snitch in and get him to talk.

02:38.159 --> 02:40.225
Won't be a problem.
He's not gonna talk.

02:40.227 --> 02:42.627
Just make sure
Pope stays with your guy.

02:42.629 --> 02:43.629
You got it.

02:43.631 --> 02:49.302
♪♪

02:49.304 --> 02:54.707
♪♪

02:54.709 --> 02:56.709
Joseph: Looks alright.

03:00.181 --> 03:02.447
Man's problem
is that he resists,

03:02.449 --> 03:07.320
and in doing so
he manifests more trouble.

03:07.322 --> 03:08.988
Faith is in acceptance.

03:11.192 --> 03:12.858
A guilty plea
with no kinda deal in place.

03:12.860 --> 03:16.595
I mean, you must be
a man of faith.

03:16.597 --> 03:18.197
Or penance.

03:18.199 --> 03:20.599
Either that or that bid
you did up in Pelican Bay

03:20.601 --> 03:22.801
was what,
Club Med to you?

03:22.803 --> 03:25.338
Did my family
put you in here?

03:25.340 --> 03:26.605
Something like that.

03:26.607 --> 03:30.943
How much does my family
have to pay you to shut up?

03:30.945 --> 03:33.212
No one's an individual
in here.

03:35.149 --> 03:38.017
Every man
<i> is</i> his association.

03:38.019 --> 03:39.218
It's not my first time.

03:39.220 --> 03:41.687
Well, then start
acting like it.

03:41.689 --> 03:44.089
You and me.
Like it or not.

03:44.091 --> 03:50.229
♪♪

03:50.231 --> 03:56.101
♪♪

03:56.103 --> 03:59.304
How was it sleeping
in your old room?

03:59.306 --> 04:00.773
Well, someone
took my pillows

04:00.775 --> 04:03.276
and switched them out
for some shitty foam ones.

04:05.580 --> 04:07.313
Check J's room.

04:09.584 --> 04:11.450
You moving back in
with Renn?

04:11.452 --> 04:13.919
Nope.

04:13.921 --> 04:17.856
She's moving down to San Antonio
with her grandma.

04:17.858 --> 04:19.592
For how long?

04:19.594 --> 04:21.526
Don't know.

04:21.528 --> 04:23.328
And what about Nick?

04:23.330 --> 04:25.998
I'm gonna go down
every couple of months.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.735
She's gonna come up here
and visit her family.

04:29.737 --> 04:31.737
Work it out.

04:31.739 --> 04:33.306
I guess.

04:36.877 --> 04:38.811
That for Pope?

04:38.813 --> 04:42.081
Yeah. Some books.
Underwear.

04:42.083 --> 04:44.684
All that county-issued stuff
is shit.

04:51.092 --> 04:53.492
What's that for?
His commissary.

04:53.494 --> 04:55.360
I already put a bunch
on his commissary.

04:55.362 --> 04:57.663
Alright, well,
then put some more on.

05:03.704 --> 05:05.771
You should visit him.

05:05.773 --> 05:07.406
It's been weeks.

05:11.446 --> 05:13.646
What the hell, Smurf?
You opened my mail?

05:13.648 --> 05:16.315
Oh, shit. Yeah, sorry.
It said SAT.

05:16.317 --> 05:17.850
I thought it was
a credit card company.

05:17.852 --> 05:20.853
Yeah, it's not.

05:20.855 --> 05:22.988
Looks like you got
a good score.

05:22.990 --> 05:24.857
94th percentile.

05:29.396 --> 05:32.397
If you want
to kiss teachers' asses

05:32.399 --> 05:38.137
and spend another four years
in the library, be my guest.

05:38.139 --> 05:41.006
I just wanted to see
what I would get.

05:41.008 --> 05:43.676
Don't open my mail again.

05:43.678 --> 05:45.878
I need you and Pope
to do a run.

05:48.215 --> 05:50.283
Fiber-optics job.

05:50.285 --> 05:52.351
Thought Baz
was handling that.

05:52.353 --> 05:54.887
Yeah, Baz is working
his ass off

05:54.889 --> 05:56.489
putting the whole job
together,

05:56.491 --> 05:59.859
and I need you guys
to do one errand.

06:04.165 --> 06:05.230
Come on.

06:05.232 --> 06:08.501
It'll be good
for your college essays.

06:08.503 --> 06:13.105
Just think of it as, uh,
extracurricular activity.

06:17.444 --> 06:18.643
Fine.

06:18.645 --> 06:23.316
♪♪

06:23.318 --> 06:26.251
[ Man whistling,
indistinct talking ]

06:26.253 --> 06:32.191
♪♪

06:32.193 --> 06:34.994
Guard: Kitchen detail!
Let's go!

06:34.996 --> 06:37.596
The rest of you got 15
before lockdown.

06:37.598 --> 06:44.670
♪♪

06:44.672 --> 06:48.473
Hey! The phrase is "excuse me,"
you jack-off.

06:48.475 --> 06:55.480
♪♪

06:55.482 --> 06:58.417
One option is to beg
for leniency at sentencing.

06:58.419 --> 07:01.687
Claim that Andrew pled guilty
because he's truly remorseful.

07:01.689 --> 07:04.357
Talk about his abusive mother,
tough childhood.

07:04.359 --> 07:08.227
Okay. So then what?
He gets life?

07:08.229 --> 07:10.229
25 to life.
But he does 20.

07:10.231 --> 07:13.298
Maybe even 15.
Paroled while he's still young.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.368
What else you got?

07:15.370 --> 07:17.169
We can seek
to change the plea.

07:17.171 --> 07:19.638
J: He shouldn't have pled guilty
to begin with.

07:19.640 --> 07:22.107
Confession was bullshit.
Coulda fought it.

07:22.109 --> 07:23.442
Andrew wouldn't listen.

07:23.444 --> 07:25.711
Well, wasn't that your job
to make him listen?

07:25.713 --> 07:29.048
Uh, no.
That's not how this works.

07:29.050 --> 07:30.983
But we can use that.

07:30.985 --> 07:32.517
We convince the judge

07:32.519 --> 07:34.387
that Andrew wasn't afforded
effective counsel

07:34.389 --> 07:37.923
both when he was interrogated
and during the pre-trial phase.

07:37.925 --> 07:40.659
Especially troubling given
his mental health challenges.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.995
Wait. Sorry. What --
What does his mental health

07:42.997 --> 07:44.863
have to do
with any of this?

07:44.865 --> 07:46.065
We have
the hospital records

07:46.067 --> 07:48.133
from his psychiatric hold
last year.

07:48.135 --> 07:50.002
Andrew has
a documented history

07:50.004 --> 07:51.670
of being disconnected
from reality.

07:51.672 --> 07:53.005
So?

07:53.007 --> 07:54.339
So it's enough
to raise suspicion

07:54.341 --> 07:55.741
about his ability
to understand

07:55.743 --> 07:57.209
what the detectives
were asking him

07:57.211 --> 07:58.543
or what he was signing.

07:58.545 --> 08:00.679
It sounds like, uh,
a lot to prove.

08:00.681 --> 08:02.748
No, we don't need
to prove anything.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.149
We just need
to raise the question

08:04.151 --> 08:05.484
why none of this
was presented to the judge

08:05.486 --> 08:07.219
ahead of Andrew
making a plea.

08:07.221 --> 08:10.155
Okay.
And that'll be enough?

08:10.157 --> 08:11.624
As long as Andrew's
on board.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.360
[ Sighs ]

08:15.362 --> 08:16.962
And the most damaging thing
they have

08:16.964 --> 08:18.231
is Amy Wheeler's
statement

08:18.233 --> 08:20.365
that Andrew described
the crime to her.

08:20.367 --> 08:21.501
Well, who's that?

08:23.104 --> 08:26.038
A woman that your brother
had a relationship with.

08:28.375 --> 08:30.509
She a credible witness?
Celia: She could be.

08:30.511 --> 08:32.511
It's murder one, and they
have a signed confession.

08:32.513 --> 08:34.980
It's going to be
an uphill battle.

08:34.982 --> 08:36.582
It's not gonna be cheap.

08:36.584 --> 08:38.317
How much?

08:38.319 --> 08:40.319
At least 100 grand
if we go to trial.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.523
Okay.
Um...thank you.

08:44.525 --> 08:46.325
-We'll be in touch.
-Alright.

08:46.327 --> 08:48.995
-Sounds good.
-Let us know what you decide.

08:56.938 --> 08:59.138
Pope's screwed.

08:59.140 --> 09:00.806
That's not what I heard.
[ Door opens ]

09:00.808 --> 09:02.942
Yeah?
Were you listening?
[ Door closes ]

09:02.944 --> 09:04.743
They just put lawyer spin
on it, man.

09:04.745 --> 09:05.878
He's gonna do life.

09:05.880 --> 09:07.346
Yeah, Pope's not
gonna make it.

09:07.348 --> 09:09.482
He won't last that long.

09:09.484 --> 09:11.416
With his mental issues,
they're gonna be pumping him

09:11.418 --> 09:12.818
full of psychotropics.

09:12.820 --> 09:14.153
They're gonna put a snitch
in his cell

09:14.155 --> 09:16.088
to get him
talking about us.

09:16.090 --> 09:17.556
Who knows what he'll say
on all those drugs?

09:17.558 --> 09:19.692
He's not gonna
say shit, J.

09:19.694 --> 09:21.026
You don't know that.

09:21.028 --> 09:22.361
I know my brother.

09:22.363 --> 09:23.829
You don't know shit,
because he's already

09:23.831 --> 09:26.165
admitted to something
when he didn't need to.

09:26.167 --> 09:28.501
He wanted to get it out.
He pled guilty.

09:28.503 --> 09:30.703
I mean, maybe he's feeling
guilty about all of it, right?

09:30.705 --> 09:32.104
Everything
that we've ever done.

09:32.106 --> 09:33.638
No, Pope ain't no snitch.

09:33.640 --> 09:34.907
You don't know that!

09:34.909 --> 09:36.309
[ Sighs ]

09:36.311 --> 09:37.910
We'll keep paying Finnigan
to make sure they don't

09:37.912 --> 09:41.046
put anybody like that
in the cell with Pope, okay?

09:41.048 --> 09:43.048
We'll take our best shot
with this lawyer.

09:43.050 --> 09:44.183
A hundred grand?

09:44.185 --> 09:46.051
And that's just to get us
to trial.

09:46.053 --> 09:49.188
Pope would do anything
for us.

09:49.190 --> 09:50.523
Even you.

09:50.525 --> 09:52.124
It's not about
the money, J.

09:52.126 --> 09:54.259
Craig:
What about the judge?

09:54.261 --> 09:56.128
We got any dirt on him
that we can use?

09:56.130 --> 09:57.596
Or better yet, the DA.

09:57.598 --> 09:59.665
Then we all go to jail
for obstruction.

09:59.667 --> 10:01.534
Hey, you don't want to be
part of the family, J?

10:01.536 --> 10:03.402
-You can leave.
-God damn it, shut up.

10:03.404 --> 10:06.138
Anytime, bro.
Guys, this is Pope
we're talking about.

10:06.140 --> 10:08.941
And we gotta do what
we need to do to get him out,

10:08.943 --> 10:10.209
but this shit
takes time, okay?

10:10.211 --> 10:11.611
We got to think
this shit through.

10:15.482 --> 10:17.250
Then we break him out.

10:20.154 --> 10:22.154
What?

10:22.156 --> 10:24.657
We can't just leave him
inside, man.

10:28.095 --> 10:30.563
What about this Amy?

10:30.565 --> 10:32.965
She's the real problem,
right?

10:32.967 --> 10:34.499
And Lena.

10:34.501 --> 10:40.706
♪♪

10:40.708 --> 10:43.242
I'll talk to Pope
about Amy.

10:43.244 --> 10:44.644
But no kids.

10:46.714 --> 10:47.580
Jesus.

10:53.554 --> 10:56.021
Julia: Where are we
supposed to go?

10:56.023 --> 10:57.156
Look.

10:57.158 --> 10:59.424
Wow. I didn't think your voice
actually worked.

10:59.426 --> 11:01.727
You haven't said a word
the entire ride here.

11:06.501 --> 11:08.968
[ Engine shuts off ]

11:08.970 --> 11:10.203
The thing with Baz...

11:11.706 --> 11:14.439
...sorry, okay?

11:14.441 --> 11:15.708
It's weird for you
'cause you're my brother,

11:15.710 --> 11:18.377
but it's not actually weird,
okay?

11:18.379 --> 11:20.645
It's, like, normal.

11:20.647 --> 11:22.315
[ Engine starts in distance ]

11:22.317 --> 11:24.917
[ Footsteps approach ]

11:24.919 --> 11:27.320
Reggie says there's six spools
for you today.

11:27.322 --> 11:29.989
You'll need this
to get out.

11:29.991 --> 11:30.890
Thanks.

11:35.062 --> 11:36.595
These things
are worth money?

11:36.597 --> 11:41.000
I thought they were just used
for backyard tables.

11:41.002 --> 11:42.735
I'm gonna help them out.

11:42.737 --> 11:43.836
Andrew.

11:44.939 --> 11:46.572
[ Truck door closes ]

11:50.077 --> 11:51.276
Deran: Hey.

11:51.278 --> 11:56.682
♪♪

11:56.684 --> 11:58.651
I brought you the stuff
you asked for.

12:02.023 --> 12:03.623
Thanks.

12:06.493 --> 12:07.660
You okay?

12:09.830 --> 12:11.797
Yeah, just keeping
my head down.

12:15.370 --> 12:17.537
It's loud in here.

12:20.041 --> 12:21.807
Did you hear that?

12:23.978 --> 12:26.412
You know you got friends
in here, right?

12:28.449 --> 12:30.983
I don't need
any friends.

12:30.985 --> 12:36.521
That's okay, but just
make sure that they, uh --

12:36.523 --> 12:37.590
they can do
what they need to do.

12:37.592 --> 12:39.925
I just want
to be left alone.

12:39.927 --> 12:42.194
Guy never shuts up.
I can't concentrate.

12:42.196 --> 12:43.528
I can't sleep.

12:43.530 --> 12:45.064
That's why we're paying
these guys,

12:45.066 --> 12:48.668
so they can, you know, make sure
that that happens, okay?

12:51.138 --> 12:53.338
The lawyers are saying that
they can get you out of this.

12:53.340 --> 12:55.608
You just got to
change your plea.

12:55.610 --> 12:57.510
I don't want
to get out of it.

12:59.947 --> 13:03.949
So you're just -- you're just
okay with pleading guilty, then?

13:03.951 --> 13:06.351
What difference does it make?
25 years to life,

13:06.353 --> 13:07.953
that's the difference it makes.
They give me what they give me.

13:07.955 --> 13:09.354
Whatever they give me
is what they give me.

13:09.356 --> 13:12.491
Hey, you need to get your head
out of your ass, Pope.

13:12.493 --> 13:14.159
Listen to me.

13:14.161 --> 13:17.063
We're trying to get you
out of here, but if you can't --

13:21.769 --> 13:23.636
You can fight this thing
at trial.

13:23.638 --> 13:26.371
No, no! No!

13:26.373 --> 13:27.906
No.
I don't want a trial.

13:27.908 --> 13:31.043
The lawyers said that they can
get your confession thrown out.

13:31.045 --> 13:34.046
Okay?
Thrown out.

13:34.048 --> 13:36.515
The only thing standing in the
way is that they said testimony

13:36.517 --> 13:38.383
from some woman named --
named Amy.

13:38.385 --> 13:40.119
Amy is not some woman,

13:40.121 --> 13:41.921
and I do not want her
to have to testify.

13:41.923 --> 13:43.456
Or Lena, okay?

13:43.458 --> 13:45.358
Cath was her...

13:58.072 --> 14:01.206
I don't want Lena
to have to hear about it.

14:01.208 --> 14:02.675
Or see it.

14:02.677 --> 14:05.611
There's pictures, you know,
from when they...

14:05.613 --> 14:06.612
dug up the body.

14:06.614 --> 14:08.347
And -- And Amy.

14:08.349 --> 14:10.349
They threatened Amy.

14:10.351 --> 14:12.552
They said
she was an accessory.

14:16.357 --> 14:20.293
What if Amy
doesn't have to testify?

14:20.295 --> 14:22.662
No. A lawyer
can't promise that.

14:26.501 --> 14:30.303
[ Sighs ] What if Amy
doesn't make it to trial?

14:30.305 --> 14:32.037
No.

14:32.039 --> 14:35.107
Look, we're worried
about this Amy.
No!

14:35.109 --> 14:41.046
♪♪

14:41.048 --> 14:42.181
Just think about it.

14:42.183 --> 14:44.183
Nothing happens to Amy.

14:44.185 --> 14:46.385
Or Lena.

14:46.387 --> 14:48.421
Do I make myself clear?

14:53.060 --> 14:54.026
Guard!

14:55.863 --> 14:57.462
Don't come back.

14:57.464 --> 15:05.738
♪♪

15:05.740 --> 15:09.474
Hey, it's J.
Can you call me back?

15:09.476 --> 15:11.544
There's a couple grand in it
for you.

15:13.480 --> 15:15.014
Sorry I'm late.

15:15.016 --> 15:17.683
I just dropped off a load
of those video game systems

15:17.685 --> 15:19.685
everybody's been
clamoring about.

15:19.687 --> 15:22.287
I thought this was
about sneakers.
It is.

15:22.289 --> 15:23.889
Okay,
so what's the deal?

15:23.891 --> 15:25.490
After they come off the boat,
most of these shoes,

15:25.492 --> 15:27.960
they -- they run through
a distro center in Hemet.

15:27.962 --> 15:29.762
Our company handles
the West Coast drops.

15:29.764 --> 15:33.032
9 times out of 10,
those drops are my route.

15:33.034 --> 15:34.833
So we either hit
the distro center,

15:34.835 --> 15:37.970
we hit the store,
or we hit you?

15:37.972 --> 15:39.705
You got it.
Need someone to rob me.

15:39.707 --> 15:42.241
Make it look real.

15:42.243 --> 15:44.710
Do you stop anywhere along
the way that's not a store?

15:44.712 --> 15:45.911
Truck stops.

15:45.913 --> 15:47.913
No, no. That's, uh --
That's too crowded.

15:47.915 --> 15:50.115
I mean something
more like a rest stop.

15:50.117 --> 15:52.185
Somewhere you just jump out
to take a piss.

15:52.187 --> 15:54.853
Not too many people around.

15:54.855 --> 15:57.656
Yeah. There's one
in Central Valley.

15:57.658 --> 15:59.925
Only got porta-potties.
No one ever stops there.

15:59.927 --> 16:01.460
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

16:01.462 --> 16:03.062
That's perfect.

16:03.064 --> 16:05.664
You pull in,
we'll do the rest.

16:05.666 --> 16:06.833
Yeah.

16:08.936 --> 16:10.135
Hey.

16:10.137 --> 16:12.738
Yeah, I need you
to find someone for me.

16:12.740 --> 16:15.241
Her name's Wheeler.
Amy Wheeler.

16:18.479 --> 16:20.213
He didn't seem
like himself.

16:20.215 --> 16:23.482
He was saying it was loud
when it wasn't.

16:23.484 --> 16:25.484
He just doesn't
look good.

16:25.486 --> 16:29.088
I mean, wouldn't that make you
want to get out of there?

16:29.090 --> 16:33.092
This thing with Amy, man,
if he doesn't like it, then...

16:33.094 --> 16:36.429
we're just gonna have to
talk to him.

16:36.431 --> 16:39.565
No. Pope doesn't want this shit
to go to trial, okay?

16:39.567 --> 16:40.766
He doesn't want
to have to put Lena

16:40.768 --> 16:42.635
through any of this stuff
right now.

16:46.173 --> 16:48.307
Well, man, I don't --

16:48.309 --> 16:49.642
My board.
What?

16:49.644 --> 16:51.811
The -- The board I got
from Trey, it's gone.

16:53.914 --> 16:56.048
Craig: Yo, the cash register's
alright.

16:56.050 --> 16:57.316
God damn it.

16:57.318 --> 17:00.453
They took a sledgehammer
to the back door lock.

17:00.455 --> 17:02.187
Yo, you check the safe?

17:02.189 --> 17:04.657
I cleaned out all the cash
I had in here already.

17:04.659 --> 17:06.058
You see, man.

17:06.060 --> 17:07.326
You know,
now that Pope's gone,

17:07.328 --> 17:09.394
people are gonna
start testing us.

17:09.396 --> 17:12.064
We got to shut this down, man.
Quick.

17:12.066 --> 17:19.872
♪♪

17:19.874 --> 17:21.406
Hey, Smurf.

17:21.408 --> 17:23.208
Hey, baby.

17:23.210 --> 17:26.612
Oh.
This is Jess and Melissa.

17:26.614 --> 17:30.415
-Hey.
-Melissa and Jess.

17:30.417 --> 17:33.018
Melissa: Nice place.

17:33.020 --> 17:36.889
Smurf: You lined up the buyers
for the fiber-optics job.

17:36.891 --> 17:40.326
You set up
all the logistics.

17:42.763 --> 17:48.267
Now it's time
for your reward.

17:49.570 --> 17:52.371
I'm really proud
of you, baby.

17:52.373 --> 17:53.639
Charley: Baz?

17:53.641 --> 17:55.107
Smurf: Drink.

17:55.109 --> 17:56.642
Hey, Smurf.

17:56.644 --> 17:58.243
This is Charley.

17:58.245 --> 17:59.512
Hey.

17:59.514 --> 18:02.114
Heard so much
about you.

18:02.116 --> 18:03.216
Oh.

18:05.320 --> 18:07.652
Aren't you beautiful?

18:07.654 --> 18:09.355
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.

18:11.859 --> 18:14.593
Do you like to party?

18:14.595 --> 18:17.062
Uh, yeah.

18:17.064 --> 18:19.264
Sure.

18:19.266 --> 18:20.800
Perfect.

18:24.339 --> 18:27.206
Hey, what up, bro?

18:27.208 --> 18:30.475
I know you fell off the wagon,
but damn.

18:30.477 --> 18:31.744
A bar.

18:31.746 --> 18:34.613
I was riding by
and saw your bike out front.

18:34.615 --> 18:36.182
Need something?

18:37.685 --> 18:39.252
So how you been?

18:41.356 --> 18:42.955
Been busy, man.

18:46.160 --> 18:48.493
Let me help you get back
on that path, man.

18:48.495 --> 18:50.563
[ Scoffs ] I'm good.

18:50.565 --> 18:52.097
You sure about that?

18:52.099 --> 18:54.233
Yeah.
Man, your shit don't work.

18:54.235 --> 18:57.770
Alright. Holler at me
if you change your mind.

18:57.772 --> 19:00.305
Once you get back
on the right path,

19:00.307 --> 19:02.642
it ain't as hard
as it seems.

19:04.379 --> 19:05.644
Alright.

19:05.646 --> 19:06.746
Alright.

19:08.783 --> 19:11.217
[ Engine starts ]

19:16.057 --> 19:18.523
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:18.525 --> 19:27.933
♪♪

19:27.935 --> 19:37.076
♪♪

19:37.078 --> 19:41.180
I want to be
left alone, okay?

19:45.552 --> 19:46.819
I'm not asking.

19:46.821 --> 19:55.294
♪♪

19:55.296 --> 20:03.769
♪♪

20:03.771 --> 20:05.304
[ Grunts ]

20:05.306 --> 20:07.039
[ Alarm blaring ]

20:07.041 --> 20:09.442
[ Indistinct shouting ]

20:09.444 --> 20:14.947
♪♪

20:21.088 --> 20:22.487
Where's the surfboard?
What?

20:22.489 --> 20:23.822
Where's the goddamn
lightning bolt?

20:23.824 --> 20:25.158
You stole it!

20:25.160 --> 20:28.161
-Stop!
-Break it up!

20:28.163 --> 20:31.364
What is wrong with you?
Stop.

20:31.366 --> 20:35.234
What are you even
talking about?

20:35.236 --> 20:39.238
All I've done for you is
be loyal and kept my mouth shut.

20:41.175 --> 20:43.709
Sorry.

20:43.711 --> 20:45.178
Sorry.

20:47.982 --> 20:49.915
There's a lot
going on right now.

20:49.917 --> 20:51.284
Yeah, I know.

20:53.120 --> 20:57.023
People have heard about Pope
and what happened to Cath.

21:00.527 --> 21:03.929
So, what,
this is about Pope?

21:03.931 --> 21:05.731
I don't know, man.

21:05.733 --> 21:07.400
It's everything.

21:07.402 --> 21:09.001
Adrian's still missing.

21:09.003 --> 21:11.870
Baz's Cath was missing.

21:11.872 --> 21:14.407
People talk.

21:14.409 --> 21:18.877
They had questions before,
but now some of them are angry.

21:18.879 --> 21:21.346
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:21.348 --> 21:26.619
♪♪

21:26.621 --> 21:32.357
♪♪

21:32.359 --> 21:34.427
[ Pounding ]

21:34.429 --> 21:37.696
♪♪

21:37.698 --> 21:40.399
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:43.370 --> 21:45.037
Oh.

21:45.039 --> 21:46.839
Here he is.

21:49.844 --> 21:50.976
Brought you a present.

21:50.978 --> 21:53.312
[ Sighs ]

21:53.314 --> 21:54.847
I dabbled in it
a little bit,

21:54.849 --> 21:58.517
but, uh,
there's still plenty left.

21:58.519 --> 22:00.585
[ Bag thuds ]

22:00.587 --> 22:02.021
Again.

22:03.724 --> 22:05.158
Huh?

22:08.062 --> 22:09.328
You're welcome.

22:15.136 --> 22:18.537
I just, uh,
finished this up today.

22:18.539 --> 22:20.739
[ Exhales sharply ]

22:20.741 --> 22:22.875
Spent two years on it.

22:22.877 --> 22:25.744
Just got my final part
today.

22:25.746 --> 22:27.880
Gonna be nice and loud.

22:27.882 --> 22:30.383
Come on.
You gonna do this or what?

22:33.154 --> 22:35.154
Expensive way
to make a point.

22:35.156 --> 22:37.290
Come on, man.

22:37.292 --> 22:41.026
I know that you talk
this shit, but...

22:41.028 --> 22:43.529
I know that it calls you.

22:47.101 --> 22:50.102
Yeah, I know this calls you,
like it calls me.

22:54.775 --> 22:55.908
Yeah, it does.

22:55.910 --> 22:57.242
Yeah.

22:57.244 --> 22:59.044
Don't mean
you gotta answer.

22:59.046 --> 23:05.918
♪♪

23:05.920 --> 23:07.553
You know what?

23:09.724 --> 23:11.157
Change of plans.

23:13.127 --> 23:15.861
I'mma get my stuff.

23:15.863 --> 23:17.730
You and me are gonna
take a ride.

23:17.732 --> 23:21.667
♪♪

23:21.669 --> 23:23.102
[ Sniffs ]

23:26.874 --> 23:28.608
Call me
if it happens again.

23:32.079 --> 23:34.413
800 bucks
for a broken lock.

23:34.415 --> 23:36.281
Goddamn racket.
[ Door opens ]

23:36.283 --> 23:38.751
Did you see Pope?

23:38.753 --> 23:40.419
Yeah.
[ Door closes ]

23:40.421 --> 23:43.556
He doesn't want
to go to trial.

23:43.558 --> 23:46.491
What about this Amy?

23:46.493 --> 23:49.362
He told us
to stay away from her.

23:49.364 --> 23:50.295
So?

23:50.297 --> 23:51.564
He's in there,
we're out here.

23:51.566 --> 23:53.966
We can deal with him
when he's out.

23:53.968 --> 23:55.701
What are you saying?

23:55.703 --> 23:58.571
I don't give a shit what
Pope wants or doesn't want.

23:58.573 --> 24:00.305
He put us
in this situation.

24:00.307 --> 24:03.709
We decide what needs to happen
and how we do it.

24:03.711 --> 24:05.177
Not him.

24:05.179 --> 24:07.313
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

24:10.451 --> 24:11.951
Oh, shit.

24:14.055 --> 24:15.921
Yo?

24:15.923 --> 24:17.656
What?

24:17.658 --> 24:18.991
Hey, slow down.
Slow down.

24:18.993 --> 24:20.693
What?
What happened?

24:23.264 --> 24:26.065
Is he okay?
Is he okay?

24:28.669 --> 24:30.203
Oh, God.

24:30.205 --> 24:33.205
Alright, alright.
Thank you.

24:33.207 --> 24:35.808
Who was that?

24:35.810 --> 24:37.610
Pope got stabbed.

24:37.612 --> 24:38.944
What?

24:38.946 --> 24:41.880
[ Sighs ] He's fine.
He just needs some stitches.

24:41.882 --> 24:44.617
Shit. Uh...alright.
Let me talk to Finnigan.

24:44.619 --> 24:45.751
I'll figure it out.

24:45.753 --> 24:47.753
I'm gonna go talk
to the Trujillos.

24:47.755 --> 24:57.096
♪♪

24:57.098 --> 25:00.132
Smurf sending you off
with that woman was screwed up.

25:01.769 --> 25:04.637
She was just trying to get back
at me for being with Baz.

25:09.243 --> 25:11.544
That was your first time,
right?

25:15.583 --> 25:18.250
That's not how it's
supposed to happen.

25:18.252 --> 25:19.919
I-I need you
to know that.

25:19.921 --> 25:25.658
♪♪

25:25.660 --> 25:27.460
Look, if you want me
to talk about something else,

25:27.462 --> 25:30.129
you need to speak up, or else
I'm just gonna keep going.

25:30.131 --> 25:35.334
♪♪

25:35.336 --> 25:38.070
I learned
how to kickflip.

25:38.072 --> 25:39.538
Yeah?

25:39.540 --> 25:41.607
Yeah.

25:41.609 --> 25:43.776
See, talking to me
ain't so bad.

25:45.412 --> 25:47.213
I love talking to you.

25:49.083 --> 25:50.949
This is what's important
to me, Andrew.

25:50.951 --> 25:53.352
Me and you.

25:53.354 --> 25:56.155
No matter what happens
with Baz or Smurf

25:56.157 --> 25:57.790
or anybody else, okay?

26:00.161 --> 26:02.962
It's always you and me.

26:02.964 --> 26:06.032
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:21.582 --> 26:25.650
Me letting something happen
to you is bad business.

26:25.652 --> 26:27.086
Don't pull
that shit again.

26:28.323 --> 26:29.855
Joseph: You okay?

26:29.857 --> 26:31.991
I'm fine.

26:31.993 --> 26:33.526
Do you have
a death wish?

26:33.528 --> 26:35.928
I mean, can you just wait until
your family stops paying us

26:35.930 --> 26:37.630
before you
get yourself killed?

26:41.068 --> 26:43.068
Those Mexicans that attacked
you, those are Varrio Ghost.

26:43.070 --> 26:45.871
I mean,
what is that about?
I can handle myself.

26:45.873 --> 26:47.673
-That right?
-You're like a broken record.

26:47.675 --> 26:50.743
Listen, if they come at you
again, let us handle it.

26:50.745 --> 26:53.679
We got more people in here
than they do.

26:53.681 --> 26:57.183
Joseph: Don't retaliate.
They'll put you in the hole.

26:59.286 --> 27:00.353
Okay.

27:02.289 --> 27:04.724
[ Engines revving ]

27:14.235 --> 27:15.500
[ Engines shut off ]

27:15.502 --> 27:17.603
[ Indistinct talking
in distance ]

27:19.440 --> 27:21.240
[ Sighs ]

27:23.044 --> 27:25.711
The hell
is this place, man?

27:25.713 --> 27:28.847
'Bout to get
our workout on.

27:28.849 --> 27:31.450
You know I own a gym,
right?

27:31.452 --> 27:33.519
One that helps you
fight that urge?

27:34.389 --> 27:36.321
[ Sighs ]

27:36.323 --> 27:39.859
[ Indistinct shouting,
cheering ]

27:39.861 --> 27:41.227
[ Laughs ]

27:50.405 --> 27:52.137
-What's up, baby?
-How you doing, big Vince?

27:52.139 --> 27:53.673
Alright.

27:56.077 --> 27:57.643
Like we agreed.

28:02.617 --> 28:04.483
What?
So you want me to fight?

28:04.485 --> 28:06.752
Man, everybody here
is fighting their demons.

28:06.754 --> 28:08.153
Why else would they fight
complete strangers

28:08.155 --> 28:10.555
in a backyard?

28:10.557 --> 28:12.491
And it's cheaper
than rehab.

28:12.493 --> 28:14.093
I suspect you got a few demons
to fight off.

28:14.095 --> 28:16.962
How? You -- You want me
to beat the crap outta someone?

28:16.964 --> 28:19.832
Is that the idea?
Not someone.

28:19.834 --> 28:21.467
Fighting me.

28:25.306 --> 28:27.106
I just put a rack
on myself.

28:27.108 --> 28:28.574
[ Chuckles ]

28:34.048 --> 28:35.614
[ Laughter ]

28:35.616 --> 28:38.684
♪<i> Yeah, I'm the secret</i> ♪

28:38.686 --> 28:41.087
♪<i> Oh, oh</i> ♪

28:41.089 --> 28:44.156
♪<i> I bet you'd like</i>
<i> this seat tonight</i> ♪

28:44.158 --> 28:48.694
♪<i> It's not a show you'll see</i>
<i> on Sundays</i> ♪

28:48.696 --> 28:51.230
Young woman:
What? I like that.

28:51.232 --> 28:53.299
Jess: What a spot.

28:53.301 --> 28:55.033
What'd you do
to get this, Baz?

28:55.035 --> 28:56.903
Eh, you know.

28:56.905 --> 28:59.037
You're a cool-ass stepmom,
Smurf.

28:59.039 --> 29:00.239
It's a hell of a gift.

29:00.241 --> 29:02.708
He earned it.

29:02.710 --> 29:07.045
You know, Baz here
has a great mind for business.

29:07.047 --> 29:08.714
Place pays for itself.

29:11.786 --> 29:13.753
You guys are all
of age, right?

29:15.055 --> 29:17.790
[ Laughter ]

29:17.792 --> 29:20.459
[ Sniffs ]

29:24.332 --> 29:27.265
♪<i> The main attraction's</i>
<i> on tonight</i> ♪

29:27.267 --> 29:30.236
[ Sniffs ]

29:31.806 --> 29:33.539
[ Chuckles ]

29:35.476 --> 29:39.545
Can I get you
another drink?

29:39.547 --> 29:40.947
Sure, baby.

29:40.949 --> 29:43.482
Great.

29:43.484 --> 29:46.485
I'll come with you.

29:46.487 --> 29:48.354
Hey.

29:48.356 --> 29:50.022
Finish this up.

29:50.024 --> 29:54.293
♪<i> Can't imagine what</i>
<i> she'll do this time</i> ♪

29:54.295 --> 29:57.296
Want another beer?

29:57.298 --> 29:58.631
You know, um...

29:58.633 --> 30:00.432
♪<i> ...than effect</i> ♪

30:00.434 --> 30:01.834
♪<i> This show isn't over yet</i> ♪

30:01.836 --> 30:03.235
Thank you.

30:03.237 --> 30:04.503
Yeah. Of course.

30:04.505 --> 30:05.704
Thank you so much.

30:05.706 --> 30:07.773
[ Sniffing ]

30:07.775 --> 30:10.909
♪<i> The main attraction's</i>
<i> still to come</i> ♪

30:10.911 --> 30:12.979
Whoo! [ Laughs ]

30:12.981 --> 30:14.446
Alright.

30:14.448 --> 30:16.315
Hey,
turn this shit up, man.

30:16.317 --> 30:18.651
[ Volume increases ]

30:18.653 --> 30:21.253
♪<i> The main attraction's</i>
<i> on tonight</i> ♪

30:21.255 --> 30:24.056
♪<i> So don't forget,</i>
<i> turn out the light</i> ♪

30:24.058 --> 30:25.724
Now I'll take another.

30:25.726 --> 30:31.129
♪♪

30:31.131 --> 30:36.468
♪♪

30:36.470 --> 30:38.337
Ding, ding.

30:38.339 --> 30:39.738
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:39.740 --> 30:42.208
You sure
you want to do this?

30:42.210 --> 30:44.276
To get sober,
you have to humble yourself.

30:44.278 --> 30:46.412
A good ass whippin'
will do that.

30:46.414 --> 30:48.247
Ain't gonna be no rematch.

30:57.625 --> 30:59.425
Alright.
Let's get out that rage.

31:02.897 --> 31:05.665
Yeah, thought I'd warm
them ribs up for you.

31:09.103 --> 31:10.502
Shit.

31:10.504 --> 31:12.805
[ Crowd cheering ]

31:14.842 --> 31:16.175
Alright, man.

31:51.079 --> 31:52.545
Get in there!

32:02.891 --> 32:04.490
[ Bell dings ]

32:04.492 --> 32:06.292
Freddie: Bell!
[ Bell dings ]

32:06.294 --> 32:07.560
Screw the bell!

32:07.562 --> 32:09.161
You said you wanted
to fight?!

32:09.163 --> 32:11.897
Hear what I said?
That's the bell!
[ Bell dings ]

32:11.899 --> 32:13.266
Back to your corner!

32:15.303 --> 32:17.103
Get off me!

32:17.105 --> 32:19.105
Get off me!

32:19.107 --> 32:22.909
I'm done!
I'm done!

32:22.911 --> 32:25.111
This is bullshit.

32:25.113 --> 32:26.913
Hey, if you walk,
you lose.

32:26.915 --> 32:28.380
I don't give a shit.

32:28.382 --> 32:35.454
♪♪

32:35.456 --> 32:36.923
Hey, Finnigan.

32:36.925 --> 32:39.325
[ Machinery whirring ]

32:41.930 --> 32:44.196
Why are we getting calls
from the infirmary?

32:44.198 --> 32:45.864
We just heard
Pope was stabbed.

32:45.866 --> 32:47.866
The jail
has to notify you.

32:47.868 --> 32:49.535
My guy says
everything is good.

32:49.537 --> 32:52.204
A few stitches.

32:52.206 --> 32:53.872
No protection, no pay.

32:53.874 --> 32:57.343
Your uncle told my guy to stay
back before he was attacked.

32:57.345 --> 32:59.478
Guy acts like
he wants to die.

33:01.616 --> 33:03.749
We put a couple of new guys
with him.

33:03.751 --> 33:05.451
It's handled.

33:12.627 --> 33:16.762
J: We might have to figure out
a different arrangement.

33:16.764 --> 33:18.897
Finnigan: Oh, yeah?

33:18.899 --> 33:21.834
Yeah, if he's not
taking the protection...

33:21.836 --> 33:23.569
We can't have him in there
flying solo.

33:23.571 --> 33:26.439
He's -- He's
mentally unstable.

33:27.708 --> 33:29.709
What kind of arrangement?

33:33.514 --> 33:36.114
A more permanent one.

33:36.116 --> 33:37.683
It's gonna be expensive.

33:39.520 --> 33:41.587
And only when
I make the call.

33:43.724 --> 33:45.924
Your family's
cool with this?

33:45.926 --> 33:47.994
No, this is gonna have to
stay between me and you,

33:47.996 --> 33:52.531
but how does 25 grand sound
to make that happen?

33:52.533 --> 33:54.266
It's good.

33:54.268 --> 34:02.274
♪♪

34:02.276 --> 34:05.678
Yo.
Where you going?

34:05.680 --> 34:07.346
Home.

34:10.150 --> 34:11.950
What's the rush?

34:11.952 --> 34:14.553
Got a family and a kid
who need me, man.

34:14.555 --> 34:16.488
If you think
you hit rock bottom,

34:16.490 --> 34:18.691
then you don't know shit.

34:18.693 --> 34:21.560
I am the bottom.

34:21.562 --> 34:24.530
That's how I was raised.
It's who I am.

34:27.635 --> 34:30.236
Dying is the only thing
at the end of that path, bro.

34:30.238 --> 34:37.509
♪♪

34:37.511 --> 34:45.051
♪♪

34:45.053 --> 34:47.185
[ Brakes squeal ]

34:47.187 --> 34:49.588
[ Engine shuts off ]

34:49.590 --> 34:50.656
Looks good.

34:50.658 --> 34:53.259
Think I can get more
next week?

34:53.261 --> 34:54.927
We just drive and collect.

34:54.929 --> 34:58.264
So, if I piss Smurf off,
does she send you two out?

34:58.266 --> 35:00.866
I'd hate to get whacked
by a high schooler.

35:00.868 --> 35:03.201
[ Chuckles ]
Better not
piss her off, then.

35:03.203 --> 35:05.538
Eh, okay, okay.

35:07.541 --> 35:09.141
Hey, load it in.

35:09.143 --> 35:15.147
♪♪

35:15.149 --> 35:20.953
♪♪

35:20.955 --> 35:23.089
[ Seat belt clicks ]
Let's go.

35:24.625 --> 35:26.025
[ Seat belt clicks ]

35:30.364 --> 35:31.897
Joseph: If we confess,

35:31.899 --> 35:34.567
he is fair and just
to forgive us our sins.

35:36.437 --> 35:40.372
There's a time and a place,
and it doesn't involve you.

35:40.374 --> 35:41.440
In due time...

35:41.442 --> 35:43.242
[ Screaming ]

35:43.244 --> 35:46.378
[ Alarm blaring,
indistinct shouting ]

35:46.380 --> 35:53.986
♪♪

35:53.988 --> 36:01.460
♪♪

36:01.462 --> 36:08.867
♪♪

36:08.869 --> 36:11.269
[ Indistinct talking ]

36:11.271 --> 36:16.209
♪♪

36:21.281 --> 36:22.881
Where's Pete?

36:22.883 --> 36:25.818
He's getting fitted
for a new glass eye.

36:25.820 --> 36:28.287
That brown one
keeps popping out.

36:28.289 --> 36:30.088
He's thinking of trying blue
this time.

36:30.090 --> 36:32.492
You know, make him
look a little scarier.

36:36.430 --> 36:37.896
[ Sighs ]

36:37.898 --> 36:40.833
No one's coming by
to blast your ass.

36:40.835 --> 36:42.901
Too many old ladies
and kids.

36:42.903 --> 36:46.104
Look, I didn't know that shit
was gonna happen with Pete.

36:46.106 --> 36:48.040
Okay?

36:48.042 --> 36:50.576
You know Pope.
He's unpredictable.

36:50.578 --> 36:51.944
Is that it?

36:54.248 --> 36:58.717
Our families have been working
together for a long time.

36:58.719 --> 37:00.719
Right?

37:00.721 --> 37:04.122
Trujillos,
the Codys together.

37:04.124 --> 37:06.725
There's gotta be a way
we can fix this problem.

37:06.727 --> 37:08.927
What problem?

37:08.929 --> 37:10.329
That's your answer?

37:10.331 --> 37:14.033
After what Pope did,
that's my answer.

37:15.603 --> 37:17.336
Tina.

37:17.338 --> 37:18.905
Name your price.

37:21.542 --> 37:23.742
[ Sighs ]

37:23.744 --> 37:28.347
♪♪

37:28.349 --> 37:31.750
You can't put a price
on respect.

37:31.752 --> 37:33.285
Your mom knew that.

37:33.287 --> 37:36.154
Kept your brother
in check.

37:36.156 --> 37:38.891
Now she's gone.

37:38.893 --> 37:41.560
Your crazy brother's
in prison.

37:41.562 --> 37:44.963
Your other brother's
a junkie.

37:44.965 --> 37:47.566
People are coming
for your weak-ass family,

37:47.568 --> 37:49.135
and it ain't just me.

37:52.373 --> 37:54.973
Respect,<i> pandejo.</i>

37:54.975 --> 37:56.709
You can't buy that.

37:56.711 --> 38:04.150
♪♪

38:09.824 --> 38:11.991
[ Footsteps approach ]

38:15.029 --> 38:17.163
What the hell
happened to you?

38:19.100 --> 38:20.666
Fight.

38:27.242 --> 38:29.374
[ Bottle opens ]

38:29.376 --> 38:30.843
[ Bottle cap clatters ]

38:30.845 --> 38:33.312
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:33.314 --> 38:35.314
[ Groans ]

38:35.316 --> 38:36.883
Pope got stabbed today.

38:39.654 --> 38:41.854
How bad?
Is he okay?

38:41.856 --> 38:45.258
Yeah. He'll be fine.
They didn't get him too bad.

38:45.260 --> 38:48.527
Some North Side San Diego
gang shit.

38:48.529 --> 38:50.329
They're affiliated
with the Trujillos.

38:50.331 --> 38:52.998
I guess they're still pissed
about what went down with Pete.

38:53.000 --> 38:54.800
What happened
to the protection?

38:54.802 --> 38:57.736
What are we
paying them for?

38:57.738 --> 38:59.338
I don't know.

38:59.340 --> 39:01.274
They said they were
gonna handle it.

39:01.276 --> 39:02.875
Well, man,
we got to do something.

39:02.877 --> 39:05.010
I tried to smooth things over
with the Trujillos.

39:05.012 --> 39:06.279
Yeah?
How'd that go?

39:06.281 --> 39:08.247
She says they're gonna
try to kill Pope.

39:11.686 --> 39:13.886
That we're weak...

39:13.888 --> 39:17.690
with Smurf dead,
Pope inside.

39:17.692 --> 39:22.828
♪♪

39:22.830 --> 39:25.364
People think we're vulnerable
right now.

39:27.368 --> 39:29.634
[ Sighs ]

39:29.636 --> 39:33.239
You know, Renn invited me to
join her in San Antonio today.

39:36.777 --> 39:39.712
Thought about it.

39:39.714 --> 39:41.780
Just don't like Texas
or Texans.

39:41.782 --> 39:47.252
♪♪

39:47.254 --> 39:52.391
♪♪

39:52.393 --> 39:54.126
Well, maybe it's time
to go.

39:54.128 --> 39:59.665
♪♪

39:59.667 --> 40:00.666
Yeah.

40:00.668 --> 40:06.539
♪♪

40:06.541 --> 40:09.041
[ Julia laughing ]

40:13.948 --> 40:15.148
Hey.
Sorry we're late.

40:15.150 --> 40:17.150
We got food
after the drop-off.

40:19.286 --> 40:20.285
Cool.

40:20.287 --> 40:22.421
[ Sighs ]

40:22.423 --> 40:24.423
Here you go.

40:24.425 --> 40:26.425
Everything went well?

40:26.427 --> 40:28.127
Piece of cake.

40:34.569 --> 40:36.369
[ Envelope rustles ]

40:38.172 --> 40:39.839
[ Envelope thuds ]

40:44.979 --> 40:46.779
Come here.

40:50.385 --> 40:52.018
Beautiful girl.

40:54.655 --> 40:59.191
I want you to pursue
your dreams.

40:59.193 --> 41:01.093
You know, school.

41:03.264 --> 41:04.931
Whatever.

41:07.001 --> 41:09.068
Just at the right time.

41:11.005 --> 41:13.873
That's all.

41:13.875 --> 41:16.341
Thanks.

41:16.343 --> 41:19.078
You know, I've been thinking
that I should focus more

41:19.080 --> 41:20.847
on what we have here, too.

41:28.890 --> 41:31.824
Okay.
Good.

41:31.826 --> 41:35.895
Hey, um, why don't you go
and get yourself a drink?

41:35.897 --> 41:37.696
Come back.
Celebrate.

41:37.698 --> 41:39.165
Alright.

41:41.236 --> 41:43.969
[ Laughs ]

41:43.971 --> 41:51.710
♪♪

41:51.712 --> 41:54.447
Ah.
Everything good?

41:54.449 --> 41:56.415
Yeah.
Yeah?

41:58.786 --> 42:05.291
I am really glad that you two
are getting along.

42:06.861 --> 42:09.929
It's good
for all of us.

42:09.931 --> 42:11.197
You know?

42:13.268 --> 42:18.003
This is
a family business.

42:18.005 --> 42:27.012
♪♪

42:27.014 --> 42:28.881
[ Grunting ]

42:28.883 --> 42:34.287
♪♪

42:36.691 --> 42:39.024
[ Breathing heavily ]

42:39.026 --> 42:40.826
Alright, open up.

42:40.828 --> 42:42.628
No!
No drugs.

42:42.630 --> 42:46.933
Look, you got two choices --
anal suppository or swallow.

42:48.970 --> 42:51.103
Alright.

42:57.845 --> 43:00.513
Open.
Tongue.

43:00.515 --> 43:01.847
Ahh!

43:01.849 --> 43:03.716
Ahh!

43:03.718 --> 43:06.251
[ Breathing heavily ]

43:06.253 --> 43:08.654
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

43:08.656 --> 43:14.860
♪♪

43:14.862 --> 43:21.000
♪♪

43:21.002 --> 43:23.268
[ Door closes ]

43:23.270 --> 43:26.038
[ Breathing heavily ]

43:33.014 --> 43:37.083
Still have a couple of weeks to
convince Pope before sentencing.

43:38.953 --> 43:41.153
It's not gonna
change his mind.

43:41.155 --> 43:44.623
I have an address for that Amy.
She's up in Orange County.

43:44.625 --> 43:47.426
DA have her in a hotel
in Santa Ana.

43:47.428 --> 43:49.895
No police protection
or anything.

43:49.897 --> 43:51.030
-No.
-Just go in there.

43:51.032 --> 43:52.632
-I can take a gun --
-No.

43:55.102 --> 43:56.969
We gotta do something.

44:02.443 --> 44:04.309
We need to break him
the hell out of there

44:04.311 --> 44:05.578
is what we need to do.

44:08.916 --> 44:10.916
How are we
gonna do that?

44:10.918 --> 44:13.052
I don't know.

44:13.054 --> 44:15.320
But we'll figure it out.
We always do.

44:15.322 --> 44:16.856
Using what?
A tank?

44:16.858 --> 44:18.524
Steal a helicopter?

44:25.066 --> 44:27.600
It's not impossible.

44:27.602 --> 44:29.334
It's like every other job.

44:29.336 --> 44:31.536
We just have to find a weakness,
and we plan it out.

44:31.538 --> 44:33.639
It's a little more complicated
than that.

44:34.875 --> 44:38.543
Means that we're done
with Oceanside.

44:38.545 --> 44:40.079
Be on the run forever.

44:40.081 --> 44:42.948
What about everything
you've built?

44:42.950 --> 44:45.550
Everything Smurf built?

44:45.552 --> 44:48.353
We can still do what we do,
just without Pope.

44:48.355 --> 44:49.955
Find a new guy.
Train him up.

44:49.957 --> 44:52.224
It's a family business, J.

44:52.226 --> 44:55.694
That's where the trust
comes from -- family.

44:55.696 --> 44:58.631
And there's no family
without Pope.

44:58.633 --> 45:07.440
♪♪

45:07.442 --> 45:09.908
He'd do it for us.
You know he would.

45:09.910 --> 45:15.180
♪♪

45:15.182 --> 45:20.519
♪♪

45:20.521 --> 45:22.121
Let's do it.

45:22.123 --> 45:23.188
Good.

45:23.190 --> 45:28.461
♪♪

45:28.463 --> 45:29.862
Okay.

45:29.864 --> 45:38.137
♪♪

45:38.139 --> 45:46.211
♪♪

45:46.213 --> 45:54.487
♪♪

45:54.489 --> 46:02.628
♪♪
